The Portrait of Henrietta Moraes, a painting by Francis Bacon, sells at Christie's for £21.3 million, the second most valuable work of post-war contemporary art sold at the London auction house. (RTÉ)The 66th Tony Awards for American theatre are held at the Beacon Theatre in New York City with Clybourne Park winning the Tony Award for Best Play and Once winning the Tony Award for Best Musical. (New York Times)